wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William Ormesby was born about 1375, his father, Richard Ormesby, was 37 and his mother, Mrs Ormesby, was 28. He married Ann Ormesby before 1428, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT 1375–":"umbes 1375–Surnud","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1428–Male":"1428–Surnud","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","1348":"1348","1400":"1400","ABT 1375":"umbes 1375","1375":"1375","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","before 1428":"enne 1428","Abt 1428":"umbes 1428","1428":"1428","Europe":"Europe","Partney, Lincolnshire, England":"Partney, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Portown, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1375–":"noin 1375–Kuollut","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1428–Male":"1428–Kuollut","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","1348":"1348","1400":"1400","ABT 1375":"noin 1375","1375":"1375","1363":"1363","1340":"1340","before 1428":"ennen vuotta 1428","Abt 1428":"noin 1428","1428":"1428","Europe":"Europe","Partney, Lincolnshire, England":"Partney, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Portown, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1375–":"environ 1375–Décédé","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","1400–Female":"1400–Décédée","1428–Male":"1428–Décédé","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1348–Female":"1348–Décédée","1348":"1348","1400":"1400","ABT 1375":"environ 1375","1375":"1375","1363":"1363",